asecd

Inverse secant of argument in degrees.

Syntax

res = asecd(x)

Input argument

x

a numeric value

Output argument

res

a numeric value

Description

asecd computes the inverse secant of argument in degrees for each element of x.

Example

R = asecd([1, 10+3i, 15+2i, 35+i])

See also

asec.

Version Description
